<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,382,838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,419,443]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
. Beddard included eight specimens in the 
<typeStatus box="[795,843,419,443]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
series. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickford" box="[931,1169,418,442]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Pickford, G. E. (1937) A monograph of the Acanthodriline earthworms of South Africa. Cambridge: W. Heffer &amp; Sons Ltd. 612 pp." type="book" year="1937">
Pickford (
<number box="[1045,1106,418,442]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1937.0">1937</number>
: 
<number box="[1118,1161,418,442]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="553.0">553</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
approved one clitellate specimen of Beddard’s 
<typeStatus box="[423,471,455,479]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
series as ‘correctly identified’ (with no number), indicating that the ‘ 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1325,454,478]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
material’ might be at the 
<collectionCode box="[322,409,491,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">BMNH</collectionCode>
, and 
<typeStatus box="[467,565,491,515]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">syntypes</typeStatus>
at the 
<collectionCode box="[638,704,491,514]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kdnf-0379" name="Zoologisches Museum Hamburg" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">ZMH</collectionCode>
. Two specimens numbered 1904.10.5.821– 
<number box="[1189,1231,490,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="822.0">822</number>
, marked as ‘Type’ are presently in the 
<collectionCode box="[401,488,527,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">BMNH</collectionCode>
, and one 
<typeStatus box="[617,704,527,551]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">syntype</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[755,821,527,550]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kdnf-0379" name="Zoologisches Museum Hamburg" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">ZMH</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Michaelsen" box="[838,1069,526,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Michaelsen, W. (1913 a) Die Oligochaeten des Kaplandes. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, 34, 473 - 556." type="journal article" year="1913" yearSuffix="a">
Michaelsen (
<number box="[990,1048,526,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1913.0">1913</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed five of Beddard’s specimens, together with two other specimens collected by E. Warren, but the present location of that material is not known. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickford" box="[454,700,598,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Pickford, G. E. (1937) A monograph of the Acanthodriline earthworms of South Africa. Cambridge: W. Heffer &amp; Sons Ltd. 612 pp." type="book" year="1937">
Pickford (
<number box="[571,632,598,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1937.0">1937</number>
: 
<number box="[646,691,598,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="553.0">553</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, one of the eight 
<typeStatus box="[915,963,599,623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
specimens proved after dissection to be 
<taxonomicName authority="Beddard, 1897" authorityName="Beddard" authorityYear="1897" box="[151,546,634,659]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Chilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lucifugus">
<emphasis box="[151,347,635,659]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Chilota lucifugus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beddard" box="[364,538,634,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Beddard, F. E. (1897) On a collection of earthworms from South Africa belonging to the genus Acanthodrilus. With an Appendix: on a new genus of earthworms belonging to the family Eudrilidae. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1897, 336 - 349." type="proceedings paper" year="1897">
Beddard, 
<number box="[478,538,634,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1897.0">1897</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Other material from Pickford collection kept at the 
<collectionCode box="[1156,1240,635,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">BMNH</collectionCode>
is marked under subspecies names, see below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,382,838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">
<bibRefCitation author="Pickford" box="[199,437,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Pickford, G. E. (1937) A monograph of the Acanthodriline earthworms of South Africa. Cambridge: W. Heffer &amp; Sons Ltd. 612 pp." type="book" year="1937">
Pickford (
<number box="[311,372,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1937.0">1937</number>
: 
<number box="[383,429,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="552.0">552</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, under the heading “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Beddard, 1897" authorityName="Beddard" authorityYear="1897" box="[669,1061,706,731]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Chilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="africanus">
<emphasis box="[669,866,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Chilota africanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beddard" box="[881,1053,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Beddard, F. E. (1897) On a collection of earthworms from South Africa belonging to the genus Acanthodrilus. With an Appendix: on a new genus of earthworms belonging to the family Eudrilidae. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1897, 336 - 349." type="proceedings paper" year="1897">
Beddard, 
<number box="[992,1053,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1897.0">1897</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
”, gives a diagnosis of the species and a key to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Beddard, 1897" authorityName="Beddard" authorityYear="1897" box="[481,931,742,766]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Chilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="africanus" subSpecies="africanus">
<emphasis box="[481,514,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">
<collectingCountry box="[481,514,742,766]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Ch</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[531,753,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">africanus africanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beddard" box="[763,931,742,766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Beddard, F. E. (1897) On a collection of earthworms from South Africa belonging to the genus Acanthodrilus. With an Appendix: on a new genus of earthworms belonging to the family Eudrilidae. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1897, 336 - 349." type="proceedings paper" year="1897">
Beddard, 
<number box="[875,931,742,766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1897.0">1897</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pickford 1937" authorityName="Pickford" authorityYear="1937" box="[992,1432,742,766]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Chilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="africanus" subSpecies="barnardi">
<emphasis box="[992,1024,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">
<collectingCountry box="[992,1024,742,766]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Ch</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1042,1256,742,766]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">africanus barnardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pickford" box="[1266,1432,742,766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" refString="Pickford, G. E. (1937) A monograph of the Acanthodriline earthworms of South Africa. Cambridge: W. Heffer &amp; Sons Ltd. 612 pp." type="book" year="1937">
Pickford 
<number box="[1373,1432,742,766]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" value="1937.0">1937</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the commencement of penial setal retractors. The subspecies are then described in detail. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1259,1406,778,803]" pageId="5" pageNumber="9">Distribution</emphasis>
of subspecies is indicated.
</paragraph>
